data.text:
Details

2 linear ft

Arranged alphabetically by ship name

This ongoing collection contains photographs of ships which have sailed in Alaskan waters from the North Pacific whaling days to the ships of the Alaska State Ferry System, including sternwheelers, schooners, fishing boats, cruise ships, gun boats, fishing boats, Revenue Cutters and others including a file of unidentified vessels. Many different photographers are represented in the collection. Photographs may duplicate Robert DeArmond's collection, PCA 134, or the Lloyd H. "Kinky" Bayers Collection, MS 10, or others
